Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper focuses on training end-to-end task-oriented dialog systems, which falls under the scope of natural language processing and computation. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a new framework for training dialog systems that incorporates supervision from various intermediate modules, which is a common approach in AI research. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses an encoder-decoder training framework, which is a common machine learning technique for sequence-to-sequence tasks like dialog generation. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering): The paper discusses the flexibility of the proposed framework for real-world deployment, which involves software engineering considerations. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper mentions a dataset of conversations between real customers and customer service agents, which suggests a focus on human-computer interaction and user experience.
